content.description:
This route climbs the left hand side of the right cave. It sort of follows a seam. It is one of the steeper routes on the B-MW. Makes a great warm-up if you have it wired or can handle a good pump.

Left side of the right cave. Shares a start with Pocket Rocket.
7 bolts and anchors.

Pocket climbing to hard to see holds and then jugs at the top. It heads right after clipping the forth bolt. Chain anchor

This is the 7th route from the left. The forth from the cave. It ends at the right set of chains.
5 bolts and anchors.

This route diagonals left along the right side of the left cave. It ends at the same anchor as They Live.

It is on the outside of the right side of the left cave. This is the forth bolted line from the left.
Bolts and anchors

Boulder out the roof and over the lip to the ledge then work right around the corner and up to the anchor of Dollman.

This route is left of Dollman and starts on the right side of the right cave and works right to the anchor of Dollman.
Bolts and anchors

This route climbs up to a small arete then onto chain anchors. Pretty good pockets, but some are hard to find at first.

This route is the 6th from the far left. 3rd from the left cave. It ends at the left set of chain anchors.
Bolts and anchors

One of the longer routes it ends on a right facing dihedral. It climbs past pretty good holds, you just need to find them. The section just before the anchors is a pile of hollow sounding blocks. Climb gently.

This route is on the wall between the two caves. It is the second on that part of the wall, just right of "Brain Damage" it is the 5th route overall from the left of the cliff.
Bolts and anchors

This route is a linkup of sorts. This route starts on Blood Beach and does a rising traverse to the 4th bolt of Hitler's Brain. The bolts you are supposed to clip are supposed to be painted black but there might not be paint still on all of them. No stars because I haven't been on it yet.

It starts on Blood Beach and finishes on Hitler's Brain.
9 bolts and anchors

The route is pretty much all huge jugs. The start traverses left then you climb up to the Supershut anchor. There is a direct start to this route that is a bit harder and climbs pretty much straight up to the anchor. 5.8 doesn't get much steeper than this. Much more solid than it looks! Sharp holds.

This route is just left of White Zombie and just right of the right cave. There is a direct start just below it.
Three bolts and anchors. This route is a bit runout but the bolts protect the hardest moves pretty well. The first bolt doesn't do much but make it harder to belay. So skip it, either with a stick clip or not. There are two more bolts for the direct start.

This is the direct start to Dollman and bumps the difficulty from 5.8 to 5.10a. If you traverse in from the right, that is the 5.8 variation. A difficult start and pocket pull lead to jugs.

Direct start to Dollman
3 bolts to anchor

Just left of Hitler's Brain and right of The Punisher. Might be a little tougher if you are short. No stars because I haven't been on it yet, it is supposed to be a pretty decent route.

10th route from the far left. 3rd route left of Blood Beach.
Bolts and anchor.

This route is just right of Hellraiser and shares and anchor with it. Power climbing on pretty good holds for the most part. Don't stray to far left and onto Hellraiser around the third bolt when the holds get small for a couple moves.

On the left side of the left cave.
Bolts and anchors

This route is an extension to Hellraiser. There is a bouldery move to get the lip of the roof. It is a bit harder since a hold broke. The grade listed is approximate.

Climb Hellraiser and keep going up through the roof.
Bolts and anchors

One of the routes often used as a warm-up. There is a big left facing flake thing about 1/3 to half way up.

This is the furthest route to the Left. It starts just left of the left cave and climbs along the edge of the cave.
Bolts and anchors

A hard start then bigger pockets lead up to a big block/shelf. Climb along the left edge of the block/shelf and through the small awkward roof to bigger holds above.

This is the second bolt line left of Blood Beach. There is an oddball bolt under the ledge/shelf that often confuses people. That bolt is the third bolt of Deadzone. This route is the 12th from the left end of the cliff.
6 bolts and anchors

Big holds separated by big moves on steep rock. Shares a start with Blood Beach but heads right at third bolt and the shelf.

Starts on the left side of the right cave. Shares a start and first three bolts with Blood Beach and then climbs just to the right of BB.
Bolts and anchors

Pretty decent holds with bad feet. Powerful. Mostly pockets. This route is probably the first or second route you will see when you get to the cliff. Big, somewhat dirty holds quickly get you into the real climbing. It ends at a wiggly pig tail and glue-in bolt anchor Many people lower off the anchor for Mars Needs Women when cleaning. Others just lower off the one wiggly pigtail.

This it the second bolt line left of Blood Beach. Or the 11th from the far left of the cliff. It is just left of "Mars Need's Women".
5 bolts and something resembling an anchor.

Steep climbing up a big flake leads to a dirty shelf and more steep climbing out of the cave on pockets. Due to frail holds stickclipping the first bolt isn't a bad idea.

Just left of Bride of the Reanimator. This is the center route in the right cave.
Many bolts and anchors

Bouldery in spots.

This route is near the center of the wall. 8th from the left. Just right of BSP and left of Hitler's Brain.
Bolts and anchors.

Link up of Bride of the Reanimator into the Reanimator. It would be a lot harder if it didn't have a good rest between the two hard parts.

Right hand cave.
Bolts and anchors

Steep climbing to pockets on the right side of the left cave. Stick clip the second bolt since the first bolt is obviously bad. I haven't been on this route yet so I didn't give it any stars. It is supposed to be quite good. A few holds have broken. Could be tough for the grade.

Right side of the left cave.
Bolts and anchors

An extension to they live. After reaching the anchor for "They Live" head up and right to the big roof. There is a bolt part way out the roof. Pull the lip and climb to the anchor. Supposedly it can be conditions dependent. I haven't been on this route yet so I didn't give it any stars.

The roof above the anchor of They Live.
Bolts and anchor

Bouldery with pretty small holds for this wall and a tough 4th clip. The route kinda zigzags at the bottom and then pretty well follows the bolts from the third up. There is a big pocket just below the third bolt. Cool moves.

Near the center of the wall. Just right of Repoman. 9th route from the left overall. 6th from the left cave. 4th from the left of Blood Beach.
5 bolts and anchors.

This is the crack that goes out the center of the left cave. I haven't done it and don't know the name. The rating is just a guess since they make you list one. It looks tough. There is a pin at the start and a couple of fixed wires along the way.

The center of the left cave.
Gear plus one fixed pin and a couple of fixed nuts. Lower off one of the sport route anchors to the side.

This route starts below a right facing corner and climbs up to a ledgy area and then trends left and up over the roof.

This route is the furthest route to the right on the B-MW
6 bolts and anchors

The first wall normally encountered at White Bluff. It has the highest concentration and a majority of the routes at WB. Most routes are about 45 to 60 feet long. Pockets tend to be the name of the game here with a few flakes, edges and big jugs mixed in. This area gets morning sun and afternoon shade. Some routes are shaded all day by the trees. It is good to avoid getting to this wall to early in the morning if it is hot. A set of 12 draws should be plenty for all the routes on this wall. Can be good on rainy days.
